## a-cli

A small, LLM-agnostic agentic chat CLI designed to run **on-device inside [a-shell](https://github.com/holzschu/a-shell)** (a non-jailbreak iOS terminal app). It gives you a usable chat/agent tool directly on an iPhone/iPad — slash commands, skill files, long-term project memory — with no jailbreak, no Linux VM, and no always-on remote box to SSH into.

**Why it exists:** the usual iOS options (iSH emulation, or SSHing into a remote machine) are either slow/battery-hungry or require an always-on server. a-cli instead is a pure-Python program that runs natively in a-shell's own interpreter and talks straight to LLM APIs over HTTPS.

**Notable design points:**
- LLM-agnostic provider layer (ships with Anthropic + OpenAI adapters)
- Reads/writes the same on-disk conventions as OpenCode/Claude Code: `.opencode/skills/<name>/SKILL.md`, `AGENTS.md`/`CLAUDE.md` memory, `.opencode/commands/<name>.md` slash commands — so a synced folder (iCloud Drive, OneDrive, Syncthing) can be shared live between your phone and PC agentic tools.
- Touch-friendly `/` command picker, `/model` and `/session` dropdowns
- Agentic file/command access scoped to the project folder, with confirm-before-run on writes/commands
- API keys stored locally only (`~/Documents/.mobilecli/secrets.json`), never in the synced folder

**Install (inside a-shell):**
```sh
lg2 clone https://github.com/dlcolby/a-cli.git ~/Documents/a-cli
cd ~/Documents/a-cli
sh bootstrap.sh
aic
```

**Usage highlights:** `/help`, `/model`, `/session`, `/skills`, `/memory`, `/mouse on|off`, `/exit`, plus any `.opencode/commands/<name>.md` file auto-becomes a `/<name>` command.

